## Protocol

- **Unit of evaluation:**
- **Development set:** Source, version, intended use, and contamination controls
- **Held-out set:** Source, version, access boundary, and sample size
- **Cases:** Nominal, boundary, adversarial, misuse, and critical regressions
- **Variants:** Model, prompt, retrieval, tools, configuration, and baseline
- **Metrics:** Definition, direction, aggregation, exclusions, and limitations
- **Acceptance threshold:** Predefined threshold and rationale
- **Uncertainty:** Variance, confidence interval, repeated runs, or reason not estimated

## Review methods

- **Human evaluation:** Rubric, reviewers, disagreement handling, and content-safety procedure
- **Model judge:** Model/configuration, calibration, judge bias, and positional controls
- **Error analysis:** Taxonomy, severity, affected users, and representative safe references

